iveness-american-foreign-policy-imperative |work=Belfer Center for Science and International Affairs |date=March 2019}}\n* {{cite news |last1=Petraeus |first1=David |last2=Serchuk |first2=Vance |title=A Return to Pointe du Hoc: The Ideas that Defined President Reagan's Approach to the World and Why They Still Matter Today |url=https://www.reaganfoundation.org/media/354713/petraeus-serchuk_d-day.pdf |work=Ronald Reagan Presidential Foundation & Institute |date=June 2019}}\n{{refend}}\n\n==See also==\n{{Portal|Biography|United States|Politics|War}}\n* [[Iraq War troop surge of 2007]]\n* [[MoveOn.org ad controversy]]\n* [[All In: The Education of General David Petraeus]]\n* [[Hood event]]\n* [[List of American federal politicians convicted of crimes]]<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/world/national-security/how-david-petraeus-avoided-felony-charges-and-possible-prison-time/2016/01/25/d77628dc-bfab-11e5-83d4-42e3bceea902_story.html|title=How David Petraeus avoided felony charges and possible prison time|first=Adam|last=Goldman|date=January 25, 2016|via=www.washingtonpost.com}}</ref>\n\n==Notes and references==\n{{Reflist|30em}}\n\n==Further reading==\n* {{cite book |last=Cloud |first=David |author2=Greg Jaffe |year=2009 |title=The Fourth Star: Four Generals and the Epic Struggle for the Future of the United States Army |publisher=Random House |isbn=978-0-307-40906-5}}\n* Robinson, Linda (2008). ''Tell Me How This Ends: General David Petraeus and the Search for a Way Out of Iraq''. PublicAffairs. {{ISBN|978-1-58648-766-9}}. plus [https://web.archive.org/web/20130511005016/http://www.pritzkermilitarylibrary.org/Home/Linda-Robinson.aspx Book Lecture] at the [[Pritzker Military Library]] on November 22, 2008\n\n==External links==\n{{Sister project links |commons=Category:David Petraeus|q=David Petraeus|s=Author:David H. Petraeus|d=Q28591|b=no|n=no|v=no|wikt=no}}\n* {{cite court\n|litigants=United States of America v. David Howell Petraeus\n|vol=\n|reporter=